## Steps

### step 1
id: open-denial-for-correction
instruction: Open the denial you want to correct (from Payments & Denials > Denials tab). The encounter detail page shows the denial card with action buttons.
success_criteria: The denial card is visible with action buttons including "Correct," "Appeal," and "Write Off."
anchor: "Correct"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Use the review-denial flow to navigate to the denial first.

### step 2
id: click-correct
instruction: Click the "Correct" button on the denial card.
success_criteria: A form or dialog has appeared asking for details about the correction (optional notes field).
anchor: "Correct"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The "Correct" button is one of the action buttons on the denial card.

### step 3
id: add-notes-and-submit
instruction: Optionally enter notes describing what you corrected (e.g., "Added missing modifier 59 to CPT 27447"). Click "Mark Corrected" to save.
success_criteria: The denial status has changed to "Corrected."
anchor: "Mark Corrected"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The notes field is optional. Click the confirmation button to save.

### step 4
id: resubmit-corrected-claim
instruction: Export a corrected 837 file from your practice management system with the fix applied, then upload it as a new batch in Altair.
success_criteria: The corrected claim has been uploaded in a new batch and is being processed.
anchor: "Upload Batch (837)"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Go to the Batches page, click "Upload Batch (837)," and upload the corrected EDI file.

## Completion Message
the denial is marked corrected and altair will watch for the resubmitted claim in the next ERA. once the payer processes it and sends payment, the encounter updates automatically.

